      <abstract displayLabel="Abstract">The Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures (CVE) vulnerability naming
                scheme is a dictionary of common names for publicly known information technology
                (IT) system vulnerabilities. It is an emerging industry standard that has achieved
                wide acceptance by the security industry and a number of government organizations.
                Federal departments and agencies should use this standard for computer vulnerability
                related activities.</abstract>
